# PHP-FIG Guide Structure

## Key Directories
- PHP-FIG implementation is in [code/php-fig-guide/](mdc:code/php-fig-guide/)
- Each PSR has its own directory under [src/](mdc:code/php-fig-guide/src/)
- Tests are in [tests/](mdc:code/php-fig-guide/tests/)
- Documentation in [docs/](mdc:code/php-fig-guide/docs/)

## Development Requirements
- Follow PSR coding standards strictly
- Use composer for dependency management
- Add PHPUnit tests for new code
- Keep implementations focused and well-documented
- Maintain backward compatibility
- Document breaking changes

## Testing and Standards
- Run tests: `composer test`
- Check coding standards: `composer check-style`
- Fix coding standards: `composer fix-style`
- Run static analysis: `composer analyze`
- Generate documentation: `composer docs`

## Implementation Guidelines
- Each PSR should be self-contained
- Use interfaces for contracts
- Implement proper type declarations
- Follow SOLID principles
- Include usage examples
- Document edge cases

